The Deputy Minister of Communications, Stella Ndabeni-Abrahams will be the keynote speaker at the City of Tshwane Media Development and Diversity Summit hosted by the Executive Mayor, Kgosientso Ramokgopa.The summit will culminate in a development compact with the media, the community, institutions of higher learning, Non-Governmental Organisations and other government agencies to collectively craft a long-term framework for media development and support as part of Tshwane Vision 2055.All members of the media are invited as follows: Date: Thursday 13 November 2014 Time: 09h00 Venue: Freedom Park The event will conclude with a media networking session in the evening.Media RSVPs should be forwarded to Ireen Magwai on Ireen@doc.gov.za or072 822 5869.Enquiries: Nthabeleng Mokitimi on 081 308 0193.Issued by Department of Communications